@NODE Int "Introduction"



@{" VMB " LINK VMB} is a Voice Mailbox System with a host of features
that will revolutionize your Amiga.

VMB has got the following features:

 - Voice messaging

 - Voice forwarding

 - Remote user access with security code protection

 - Logged all actions in a logfile

 - Zeitansage (only in German)

 - easy to use and easy to install (with Installer)


It`s really easy to use.... Plug and Play ! 


@ENDNODE
@NODE VMB "Voice-Mailbox"

Voice Mailbox System for ZVT

@ENDNODE
@NODE progs "VMB Programs"


 This archive contain following programs:

        @{"VMB-Installer" LINK ins}
        @{"VMBCT" LINK vmbct}
        @{"VMB" LINK vmbprg}

@ENDNODE
@NODE vmbct "VMB Control Tool"

        VMBCT Control Tool is the Tool to Control VMB...  ;-)


        The Menu look`s like:

         @{"Record Message" LINK Rec}     
         @{"Play Message" LINK Pla}     
         @{"View Logfile" LINK Vie}      
         @{"Delete Logfile" LINK Del}     
         @{"Create New Mailbox" LINK Cre} 
         @{"exit" LINK exi}               


@ENDNODE

@NODE Vie "View Logfile"

You can view the Logfile 

- press RETURN for the next call
- press m/RETURN for the Menu

@ENDNODE

@NODE Del "Delete Logfile"

You can delete the Logfile 

@ENDNODE


@NODE Rec "Record Message"

You can record new Systemmessages 

1.      Choose the message from the filerequester
2.      The Contens of this message appear in the window
3.      record the message

@ENDNODE

@NODE pla "Play Message"

You can play Systemmessages 

1.      Choose the message from the filerequester

@ENDNODE

@NODE Cre "Create New Mailbox" 

1.      Enter a Mailboxnumber (only 11-59 supported)
2.      Enter a Password (only 4 digits)

@ENDNODE



@NODE vmbprg "VMB Program"

The program called VMB is the Main Program.
What should i say ... hamm view the @{"Quick Reference Guide" LINK "VMBQRG/main" 0}
and you know how it work`s! 

Start it with @{" ZVT " LINK ZVT} Button "Call receiver = on" for incomming calls
or with the @{" ZVT " LINK ZVT} Button "Answer call". 

CallerVoc are stored in VMB: CALVOC

There is a test mailbox #11 with 1 message to test VMB 

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requ "Requirements"

To run @{" VMB " LINK VMB} V1.11 you need:

-An Amiga model (500/600/1000/1200/2000/2500/3000/4000/CDTV/CDł˛)
-OS 2.0 or higher
-@{" ZVT " LINK ZVT} V1.4 or higher
-@{" MUI " LINK MUI} V2.3 or higher
-ARexx server by William S. Hawes
-A ZyXEL-Modem with V5.02 ROMs or higher 
-2 MB free RAM
The following libs in your LIBS: drawer
        
        -@{" reqtools.library " LINK reqtools}
        -@{" diskfont.library " LINK diskfont}
        -@{" rexxapp.library " LINK rexxapp} 
        -@{" rexxsyslib.library " LINK rexxsys}
        -@{" rexxreqtools.library " LINK rexxreq}
        -@{" rexxsupport.library " LINK rexxsup}

-The following commands in your C directory:

        -delete
        -makedir
        -copy

@ENDNODE
@NODE sound "sound"

        "sound" is a litte tool by GRAMMA SOFTWARE to play a sample.
        
        It`s used for Operator Paging to play the sample "VMB:VMBDAT/SOUND"
        

@ENDNODE
@NODE time "Time"

        sorry Time is only in German!

        Join with DTMF 9 in the @{" VMB Mainmenue  " LINK "VMBQRG/main" 0} 

@ENDNODE
 

@NODE diskfont "diskfont.library"

You should have this file installed in you LIBS:  directory 
(if the installation hasn't already been done by the Commodore Workbench 
installation script).

You can find diskfont.library on a Workbench disk.

@ENDNODE

@NODE rexxreq "rexxreqtools.library"

VMB need the rexxreqtools.library version 37.95 or higher

RexxReqTools was written by Rafael D'Halleweyn.

You can find diskfont.library in the VMB:Libs directory.

@ENDNODE

@NODE rexxapp "rexxapp.library"

VMB need the rexxapp.library 

rexxapp.library is a PD library

You can find rexxapp.library in the VMB:Libs directory.

@ENDNODE

@NODE rexxsup "rexxsupport.library"

VMB need the rexxsupport.library version 34.9 or higher

You can find rexxsupport.library in the VMB:Libs directory.

@ENDNODE

@NODE rexxsys "rexxsyslib.library"

VMB need the rexxsyslib.library version 36.23 or higher

You should have this file installed in you LIBS:  directory 
(if the installation hasn't already been done by the Commodore Workbench 
installation script).

You can find rexxsyslib.library on a Workbench 2.0 (or higher) disk.
@endnode


@NODE reqtools "reqtools.library"

VMB need the reqtools.library version 38 or higher

About ReqTools:
ReqTools is  designed with Commodore's style guidelines in mind, all
requesters  have  the look-and-feel  of  AmigaDOS  Release  2. 
(From  the  README  file in the ReqTools distribution).                                                   
                                                                          
ReqTools is © Nico François                                               

You can find reqtools.library in the VMB:Libs directory.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Ins "Installation"



To install @{" VMB " LINK VMB}, just do the following things:


- Decrunch the archive

- Check the @{" Requirements " LINK Requ}

- if you dont start RexxMast in your User-Startup add following line:

--- cut here ---

System/RexxMast >nil:

--- cut here ---

- use the Installer called VMB-Install

- edit the line  »» ZVT location «« in the file called 'VMB.cfg' in the VMBDAT drawer 

- that`s all... 

@ENDNODE
